After carefully reviewing all the Extensions subsystem files, I found several potential issues:

```json
{
  "issues": [
    {
      "file": "cmd/sftp-server-driver.go",
      "line": 235,
      "description": "WriteAt method potential panic when accessing nextOut - if w.w.Write() fails on line 233, the function returns before updating the len(b) at line 245, causing inconsistent return value reporting"
    },
    {
      "file": "cmd/sftp-server.go",
      "line": 362,
      "description": "Logic bug in filterAlgos function - 'found' variable is not reset between iterations, causing incorrect fatal error when processing multiple algorithms where some are valid and others are not"
    },
    {
      "file": "cmd/sftp-server.go",
      "line": 432,
      "description": "Incorrect boolean parsing for password-auth - strconv.ParseBool errors are silently ignored, causing disablePassAuth to remain false even for invalid input values like 'invalid'"
    },
    {
      "file": "cmd/veeam-sos-api.go",
      "line": 102,
      "description": "XML struct tag typo - 'mxl' should be 'xml' for ProtocolCapabilities field, which will cause incorrect XML marshaling"
    },
    {
      "file": "cmd/veeam-sos-api.go",
      "line": 197,
      "description": "Potential negative capacity calculation - if ci.Used exceeds ci.Capacity, ci.Available becomes negative which may cause issues with Veeam clients expecting positive values"
    }
  ]
}
```
